---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Grant Submissions — Action Sports Safety Project"
  description="How to apply for a tuition grant covering an approved medical certification course."
>
  <Header />

  <main id="main-content">
    <section class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="grants-title">
      <div class="page-hero-inner">
        <div>
          <p class="page-hero-eyebrow" aria-hidden="true">Grant submissions</p>
          <h1 class="page-hero-title" id="grants-title">
            Apply for a tuition grant.
          </h1>
        </div>
        <p class="page-hero-lede">
          We pay the full tuition for approved medical certification courses, directly to
          the training provider. Athletes, coaches, park staff, and event organizers in
          the action sports community are eligible.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page-section">
      <div class="page-split">
        <aside class="page-aside">
          <p class="page-aside__heading">How it works</p>
          <ul class="page-aside__list">
            <li><a href="#eligibility">Eligibility</a></li>
            <li><a href="#courses">Approved courses</a></li>
            <li><a href="#process">Process</a></li>
            <li><a href="#timeline">Timeline</a></li>
            <li><a href="#apply">Apply</a></li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <div class="prose">
          <h2 id="eligibility">Eligibility</h2>
          <p>You are eligible if you can answer yes to all three:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              You are part of the action sports community as a participant, coach, park
              or shop staff member, event organizer, or guide.
            </li>
            <li>
              You will use the certification in a community setting (events, parks, shops,
              guiding, coaching, peer response).
            </li>
            <li>
              The course you are applying for is on our approved list, or you have written
              approval from us in advance.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="courses">Approved courses</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>CPR / AED (American Red Cross or American Heart Association)</li>
            <li>Wilderness First Aid (NOLS, SOLO, WMA, or equivalent)</li>
            <li>Wilderness First Responder (NOLS, SOLO, WMA, or equivalent)</li>
            <li>EMT-Basic (state-approved program)</li>
            <li>Wilderness EMT</li>
            <li>Stop the Bleed</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Have a course in mind that is not on this list? Email
            <a href="mailto:grants@actionsportssafetyproject.com">grants@actionsportssafetyproject.com</a>
            with details before applying.
          </p>

          <h2 id="process">Process</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Submit an application using the form below.</li>
            <li>
              Our Grant Review Board scores applications on community impact and financial
              need. We award based on score, not on submission order.
            </li>
            <li>
              If approved, we pay tuition directly to the training provider on your behalf.
              You register normally and attend the course.
            </li>
            <li>
              After completion, send us a copy of your certificate and a short note (a few
              sentences) on how you plan to use it.
            </li>
          </ol>

          <h2 id="timeline">Timeline</h2>
          <p>
            Applications are reviewed monthly. Decisions are sent within 30 days of the
            review meeting. Funded courses must be completed within 12 months of the
            award date.
          </p>

          <h2 id="apply">Apply</h2>
          <p>
            The online application is launching alongside our first review cycle. Until
            then, please email
            <a href="mailto:grants@actionsportssafetyproject.com">grants@actionsportssafetyproject.com</a>
            with the following:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your name, location, and the action sports community you are part of</li>
            <li>The course you want to take, the provider, and the cost</li>
            <li>How you plan to use the certification once you complete it</li>
            <li>A short note on financial need (we keep this confidential)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We respond to every email within five business days, even if our reply is
            "we need more information."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>
